    <p class="HEADINGSTYLE">CONCURRENCE</p>

    <p class="Bodycopy">I concur with the Panel's recommendation, I write separately only to explain that I do not
    necessarily agree with the Panel's statement, in connection with its comparison of Standard 4.62 with Standard
    46.61, that (Slip Op., p. 15) "... there is no showing that Respondent had the requisite intent to benefit herself
    or another." The Panel finds that (Slip Op., p. 15) Respondent "knowingly failed to perform services for Mr. Oldham
    and Ms. LeDay" and that (id.) Respondent knowingly deceived Mr. Oldham and Ms. LeDay. In my opinion, it can be
    inferred from Respondent's persistent refusal to account for and refund the unearned fees to Mr. Oldham and Ms.
    Leflay that Respondent intended to benefit herself.  However, this point is not important to the ultimate
    disposition of this case because the Panel correctly concludes that disbarment is the appropriate sanction.</p>

